FT  12 OCT 92 / International Company News: Moody's upgrades News Corp
subsidiaries' debt to Ba2, B1
MOODY'S, the US rating service, has upgraded the long-term debt of media
group News Corp subsidiaries from B1 to Ba2 for senior unsecured debt and
from B3 to B1 for subordinated debt. Preferred stock has been upgraded from
b3 to b1, Alan Friedman reports from New York.
Moody's also assigned a Ba2 rating to News America's proposed Dollars 1bn of
senior notes and debentures.
